Olivier</i>, recorded as the name of one of Charlemagne's paladins (retainers), the close companion in arms of Roland in the Chanson de Roland. Whereas Roland is headstrong and rash, Oliver is thoughtful and cautious. Ostensibly this name derives from Late Latin <i>olivarius</i> ‘olive tree’ (  compare  Olive  ), but Charlemagne's other paladins all bear solidly Germanic names, so it is more probably an altered form of a Germanic name, perhaps distantly connected with Old Norse <i>Óleifr</i> ‘ancestral relic’. It has remained in more or less continuous use since the medieval period, becoming ever more popular since the 1980s."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705189,"age":25,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705190,"age":56,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Sir Oliver Dinham was born in 1234, in Hartland, Devon, England, United Kingdom, his father, Sir Geoffrey Dinham, was 35 and his mother, Sarah Hornacote, was 20. He had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with Isabel de Vere. He died on 26 February 1299, at the age of 65, and was buried in Exeter, Devon, England."},"et":{"1234–26 February 1299":"1234–26. veebruar 1299","1234–1299":"1234–1299","1235–1299":"1235–1299","1253–1321":"1253–1321","1275–1301":"1275–1301","1200–1258":"1200–1258","1214–1302":"1214–1302","before 26 February 1275":"enne 26. veebruari 1275","1275":"1275","1253":"1253","Bef 26 December 1258":"enne 26. detsembrit 1258","1290":"1290","1259":"1259","1302":"1302","1214":"1214","1258":"1258","